As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2" /> of 2000, there were 1,695 people, 827 households, and 459 families residing in the borough.<ref name="American FactFinder"/> The population density was {{convert|3,482.5|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. There were 907 housing units at an average density of {{convert|1,863.5|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of the borough was 99.76% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0.06% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], and 0.18% from two or more races. Of the population, 0.35% were [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race.

